- **What it is**: A flag that tells your theme to use Android 12+ “Material You” dynamic colors (Monet) derived from the user’s wallpaper, instead of your app’s fixed palette.

- **When true**:
 - On Android 12+ (API 31+): Uses `dynamicLightColorScheme`/`dynamicDarkColorScheme` from the system, so colors adapt to the user’s wallpaper.
 - On Android 11 and below: Falls back to your static color scheme.

- **When false**:
 - Always uses your app’s static color scheme (your green palette), on all Android versions.

- **Effect on your UI**:
 - Your login gradient uses `MaterialTheme.colorScheme` colors. With dynamicColor=true on Android 12+, it will match the system wallpaper; with dynamicColor=false, it stays consistently green.

- **Dark mode**:
 - The `darkTheme` parameter still selects the dark or light variant, whether colors are dynamic or static.

- **Recommendation**:
 - Use `true` if you want to blend into the user’s system theme.
 - Use `false` for a consistent brand color (your green theme) everywhere.

- If you want dynamic overall but a green-only login gradient, we can override just the gradient colors while leaving `dynamicColor = true`.

- Short summary: dynamicColor=true uses wallpaper-derived colors on Android 12+, false enforces your static green palette across all devices."}]}]}

