- In your code: It’s a coroutine Job that:
 - Runs in a loop while active.
 - Calls getSpecificUser.
 - Updates the UI state.
 - Waits intervalMs (e.g., 5s), then repeats.
 - Cancels automatically when the ViewModel is cleared or when you start a new poll for a different userId.

- Why use it: Simple way to reflect backend changes without user action.

- Trade-offs:
 - Pros: Easy to implement; works with any HTTP API.
 - Cons: Extra network/battery usage; not instant. Consider push/WebSocket/SSE or Room Flow for true realtime."}]},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"
